# Hepta Design System

This project is a design system documentation site and React component library. Use it as the source of truth when building frontends.

## Packages

- `@hepta/tokens` – Design tokens (colors, spacing, typography, radius, shadow)
- `@hepta/components` – React components (Button, Input, Card)

## Imports

```tsx
import { Button, Input, Card } from '@hepta/components';
import '@hepta/tokens/css';
import '@hepta/components/styles.css';
```

## Design Tokens

- **Never use hardcoded colors, spacing, or typography.** Use CSS custom properties.
- Token reference: `packages/tokens/dist/tokens.manifest.json` – lists all tokens with light/dark values and descriptions.
- CSS variables use the `--hepta-*` prefix, e.g. `--hepta-color-text-primary`, `--hepta-spacing-4`.

## Components

- **Reference:** `packages/components/dist/components.manifest.json` – component list, props, variants, usage examples.
- All components use tokens and support light/dark theme via `data-theme` on an ancestor.

## Theming

Set `data-theme="light"` or `data-theme="dark"` on `document.documentElement` to switch themes.

## Conventions

- Use semantic token names (e.g. `color.button.primary.background`) not primitives in component logic.
- Components accept `className` and standard HTML props for overrides.
- Props follow consistent patterns: `variant`, `size`, `disabled` where applicable.
